<ns0:entry xmlns:ns0="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:ns1="http://schemas.google.com/g/2005" xmlns:ns2="http://schemas.google.com/projecthosting/issues/2009" ns1:etag="W/&quot;DE4BR347eCl7ImA9WhZREUQ.&quot;">
		<ns0:id>http://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/full/1589</ns0:id><ns0:author>
			<ns0:name>bradc...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/110304265766688778552/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
GC callbacks nacl_pre_syscall_hook and nacl_post_syscall_hooks are registered using weak symbols, with help from the nacl-ld.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
This makes the ABI surface we are trying to stabilize less regular.

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
A registration callback would be a cleaner way to expose this functionality.

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
A registration callback is available and tested, replacing the current mechanism of weak symbols.

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
One small step on the road to ABI stability.
